.SS "A first SPARQL query and rdfpuml diagram"
.PP
TODO --- expand.
.PP
This chapter introduces two of ELOT’s most-loved features:
.IP \(em 4
running \fBSPARQL\fP queries directly against your tangled \fI.omn\fP via
embedded source blocks,
.IP \(em 4
generating \fBPlantUML diagrams\fP of selected triples via the
\fIrdfpuml\-block\fP Library-of-Babel helper.
.SS "A first SPARQL block"
.PP
Add this to \fIpets.org\fP, below the class definitions:
.RS
.nf
\fC#+begin_src sparql :url "pets.omn"
,select ?s ?o where { ?s rdfs:subClassOf ?o }
#+end_src
\fP
.fi
.RE
.PP
Press \fIC\-c C\-c\fP inside the block.  ELOT shells out to ROBOT and
inserts the result table below the block.  No \fIPREFIX\fP boilerplate
needed --- ELOT injects prefixes from your \fIprefix\-table\fP.
